This paper deals with a method for reasoning about qualitative spatial and temporal information, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves generating composition tables, which is a computational task that could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions constraint propagation, which is a technique used in optimization and search algorithms, falling under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB).
